"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-19-olympics-star-defects-team-gb-paris-2024-i-hope-understand-21447812\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Three-time Australian Olympic medallist Matthew Richardson has defected to Team GB following Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.998611560151299, \"rank\": 0.0013274333007835396, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 40, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Richardson_(footballer)\", \"score\": 0.9918787924836031, \"rank\": 0.007602339181287399, \"text\": \"Matthew Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13414980\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Richardson_(footballer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Richardson_(footballer)\"}, {\"begin\": 75, \"end\": 82, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.8413371690525012, \"rank\": 0.1885840576620246, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 93, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0048391467382255e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The track cycling star won three medals for Australia at the recentOlympic Games, claiming silvers in the individual sprint and keirin as well as bronze in the team sprint.\", \"from\": 106, \"to\": 278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 150, \"end\": 159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.5521577484958592, \"rank\": 0.7607833322530514, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 234, \"end\": 240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.168676178831833e-36, \"text\": \"keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson, 25, was born in England and grew up in Kent before moving to Western Australia at the age of nine with his family.\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999994799964, \"rank\": 5.200371769511336e-10, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.5991560205019683, \"rank\": 0.4277647956605417, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_rugby_league_team\"}, {\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kent\", \"score\": 0.9922144491657388, \"rank\": 0.007840120618047926, \"text\": \"Kent\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kent\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Commonwealth Games champion has represented Australia since 2019 but has decided to switch nationality and ride for Great Britain going forward.\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 412, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"score\": 0.999908490782583, \"rank\": 8.58568539258163e-05, \"text\": \"Commonwealth Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 456, \"end\": 465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.5521577484958592, \"rank\": 0.7607833322530514, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999879148619, \"rank\": 8.756394687722238e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Announcing the decision in a post that started with the message 'the end of an era', Richardson said: 'I have made the decision to pack up my entire life and move half way across the world to begin the next chapter in my cycling career.\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 643, \"end\": 653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999994799964, \"rank\": 5.200371769511336e-10, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It is with a sense of excitement and renewal I announce I have joined the Great British Cycling Team.\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Switching nationality was a difficult decision, and not one I took lightly.\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a personal choice, made after careful consideration of my career and future.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's not something I decided on quickly or easily.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I deeply respect Australia and the Aus Cycling Team and it will always be a part of who I am.\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1131, \"end\": 1140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.5521577484958592, \"rank\": 0.7607833322530514, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999988567652, \"rank\": 9.778446154227455e-10, \"text\": \"Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'As this new chapter in my life begins, I would like to sincerely thank the coaches and support staff who have worked with me over many years in Australia.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.5521577484958592, \"rank\": 0.7607833322530514, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Special mention to Midland Cycle Club, WAIS and Aus Cycling with personal thanks to the two biggest coaching influences in my career, Clay Worthington and Matt Crampton.\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1419, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999988567652, \"rank\": 9.778446154227455e-10, \"text\": \"Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worthington_Brewery\", \"score\": 0.9999999763717827, \"rank\": 1.4300258488231909e-08, \"text\": \"Worthington\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worthington_Brewery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worthington_Brewery\"}, {\"begin\": 1522, \"end\": 1535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Crampton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Crampton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Crampton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Crampton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I want to say a huge thank you to my teammates for everything we have been through together.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'You have been there for the highs and the lows, and I am so grateful for all the support, laughter, and hard work we have shared.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'But this decision is about following my passion and pushing myself to new heights.\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'This is not about leaving something behind, but about embracing a new chapter in my journey and chasing a dream, a dream that is to race for the county in which I was born.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I hope you can understand and support me as I continue to give my best in the sport I love.'\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson, who is in a relationship with Team GB cycling star Emma Finucane, has previously hinted at the possibility of competing for the country of his birth.\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2120, \"end\": 2130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999994799964, \"rank\": 5.200371769511336e-10, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 2162, \"end\": 2169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.8413371690525012, \"rank\": 0.1885840576620246, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2183, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9996163733593958, \"rank\": 0.00033435804350320607, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen Park, performance director of GB Cycling, said: 'We are pleased to welcome Matt to the team and will be supporting him in his transition onto the programme over the coming weeks and months.\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2283, \"end\": 2295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\", \"score\": 0.9934897991810496, \"rank\": 0.005518084484569497, \"text\": \"Stephen Park\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\"}, {\"begin\": 2321, \"end\": 2323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7541820715960629, \"rank\": 0.32593974161979067, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2324, \"end\": 2331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999988567652, \"rank\": 9.778446154227455e-10, \"text\": \"Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'We are incredibly proud of our sprint programme, which has delivered some fantastic results at the recent Olympic Games and continues to go from strength to strength.\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Matt will only be adding to this strength in depth and I am excited to see what his presence adds to the talent we already have as we start to turn our attention to the new four-year cycle\\u00a0towards LA 2028.'\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2849, \"end\": 2856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LA 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 2860, \"to\": 2908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Team GB Paris Olympics hero angers rival with 'classless' celebration  ArrowMORE:Eddie Hearn offers to promote Imane Khelif after Olympic boxing gender row  ArrowMORE:Top 10 athletes who won the most prize money at the Olympics  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straigh